    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is doable, at least in theory, <strong>if</strong> you know the index:</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(team1.keySet().toArray()[0]);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>keySet()</code> returns a set, so you convert the set to an array.  </p>\n\n<p>The problem, of course, is that a set doesn't promise to keep your order.  If you only have one item in your HashMap, you're good, but if you have more than that, it's best to loop over the map, as other answers have done.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4645463,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 3763927,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 33,
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/100000308371643/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "user3763927",
