    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To get keys in HashMap, We have keySet() method which is present in <code>java.util.Hashmap</code> package.\nex : </p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Map&lt;String,String&gt; map = new Hashmap&lt;String,String&gt;();\nmap.put(\"key1\",\"value1\");\nmap.put(\"key2\",\"value2\");\n\n// Now to get keys we can use keySet() on map object\nSet&lt;String&gt; keys = map.keySet();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Now <strong>keys</strong> will have your all keys available in map.\nex: [key1,key2]</p>\n"
